I had the help of a 52 necro when I did the quest at level 20. Hmm... DMF.... Still using the staff at 50... *shudder*. Time for an upgrade... anybody wanna help me take out Phinny, Venril, and the BG? <p>--<br>
<center><a href="http://www.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=69019" target="_new" style="text-decoration: none; font-family: 'Arial', 'Helvetica', sans-serif; size: 12pt; color: #007fff">Aurianne Stormsummoner</a> <font style="text-decoration: none; font-family: 'Arial', 'Helvetica', sans-serif; size: 12pt; color: #007fff"><</font><a href="http://orderofantondwer.cjb.net" target="_new" style="text-decoration: none; font-family: 'Arial', 'Helvetica', sans-serif; size: 12pt; color: #007fff">Order of Antondwer</a><font style="text-decoration: none; font-family: 'Arial', 'Helvetica', sans-serif; size: 12pt; color: #007fff">><br>High Elven Wizardess of Karana</font><br><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter" target="_new" style="text-decoration: none; font-family: 'Arial', 'Helvetica', sans-serif; size: 12pt; color: #007fff">Vazaelle Server</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/26/01 5:52:54 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the Wheel</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry for anyone who gets browbeaten into thinking this is really a 20+ quest. It's a 20+ quest if you're in a guild full of higher level sorts. Otherwise, you can get the first seven pieces in your 20s, but don't feel like you need to get Oasis, Rathe and Guk until at least 30. <br>
<br>
It took the help of a level 49 shadow knight to get me safely to the hand room, and having been there since when I was in my high 40s, I see that it is just as dangerous of a trip as I thought. On Vazaelle, Lower Guk is lightly camped, with 30 people in the zone being about the peak. With that few people camping the place, it's not terribly easy to get there.<br>
<br>
Having said that, this is a great item, and a rite of passage for wizards. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-banner-long-2.gif" height=60 width=468 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umacfudd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Macfudd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/27/01 3:41:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the Wheel</span><hr size=1> Ummmm,  well.  I would have to say that level 20 really isn't that hard to finish it at.  You even have ports to speed the whole process up.  I finished it at level 16, totally untwinked and my wizard is the only character I had ever played.  I ran the whole thing on foot and without sow or any high level help with a few exceptions.  With the Unrest piece a high level Warrior sent me a tell as soon as I zoned in asking if I wanted to be shown where the piece so that was easy.  I spent about 20 minutes trying to find an entrance to Lower Guk in Upper Guk until I gave up and looked it up on eqatlas (I had to use my memory as I don't have a working printer) then spent another 15 minutes before looking it up again and then took another 10 minutes but finally found it.  I zone in, and shout &quot;Is anyone camping the Hand room or able to guide me safely there?  I need a quest item from the floor of the room.&quot;  The first time I got aggroed on and had to zone, after zoning back in I shouted again and got a reply instantly.  One of the people camping it sent me a tell to say the Staff piece had just repoped, came and gave me invis to undead and then led me through LG to the Hand room.  I grabbed it, they waved goodbye and I gated out.  Simple.  None of the other pieces gave me any trouble except the Permafrost one.  Instead of just rooting the skeletons (which were blue at 16) I panicked and ran, but was brought down.  That was the only time I died, and was rather annoying as I couldn't swim far enough to get back into the underwater cave without drowning.  While I was underwater though I passed a level 55 cleric practising swimming who went in and rezzed me.  If you are prepared to keep trying LG in peak times and wait you should get that piece without any problems.  This quest is the most enjoyable I've done so far. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uryzak620.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryzak620</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/27/01 7:49:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the Wheel</span><hr size=1> If I remember right, this is one of Whiz's favorite quests, and it is also one of mine.  What makes it great, is you don't have to kill anything!  You just have to be intuitive, careful, and smart <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
When this quest originated, there was no kunark and velious.....so Lower Guk would be camped by well over 100 people, which is about 1 person per mob :P<br>
<br>
With those kinds of numbers in the zone, it is very conceivable to get the piece in the hand room at lvl 20.  But lately, especially w/ the new robes, haste items and wpns with stupidly low delay.....lower guk is pretty empty, which makes it nigh on impossible to get this solo at a lower lvl.<br>
<br>
Anyone lvl 16 and above can do 7 of the 10 pieces with relative ease (you need 16 for invis).  The 3 difficult rods are oasis, lake rathe (for the same reason...stupid see invis gobs), and the guk one.<br>
<br>
Personally, I enjoy quests a great deal, as long as i am not camping ultra rare spawn (ie ragefire) and there is some thought put into the end result of the quest.  One of the more annoying quests I did recently was the Helsenn's Prismatic Trinket.  Took 10 hours to finish this one.  Most of it was great, but the last part waiting for that undead dorf to spawn in ToFS was simply annoying.<br>
<br>
Quests are what you make of them.  Sometimes, they are a very nice break from the mundane kill, kill, kill routine in the game<br>
<br>
